    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsing `:bdelete` on any currently open files with global or local marks deletes\ntheir marks upon closing neovim. Tested `:bufdo bd` with all globally marked\nfiles open, with disastrous results. This can be avoided if the user re-opens\nthe marked files before closing neovim.\n\nI tried to find the commit that caused the issue with git bisect. I believe\nthis to be the culprit: 6bee2f686fcfd190e7017fc08115de247ac9afe9 .\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```md\n# Marks are deleted\n\n1. nvim -u NONE\n2. :edit foo\n3. :mark X (or mX)\n4. :marks               // \"foo\" is listed\n5. :bdelete\n6. :marks               // \"foo\" is still listed\n7. :q\n8. nvim -u NONE\n9. :marks               // \"foo\" is gone\n\n# Marks persist\n\n1. nvim -u NONE\n2. :edit foo\n3. :mark X (or mX)\n4. :edit bar\n5. :mark Y (or mY)\n6. :marks               // \"foo\" and \"bar\" are listed\n7. :bufdo bdelete\n8. :marks               // \"foo\" and \"bar\" are still listed\n9. :edit foo            // Reloading \"foo\" prevents the bug\n10. :q\n11. nvim -u NONE\n12. :marks              // \"foo\" is listed, but \"bar\" is gone\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMarks are not deleted by `:bdelete`, as that concerns `:bwipeout`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1264d11\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian 13\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.41.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbob-nvim",
